<2> The quarter, featuring George Washington’s profile and “UNITED STATES OF AMERICA,” provides scale to the miniature USB module.  
<3> The red PCB has labeled pins (P1 to P4) and a gear icon, indicating its use in DIY electronics or microcontroller setups.  
<4> The USB connector’s metallic housing and internal contacts suggest it’s designed for reliable data transfer and power delivery.  
<5> The image highlights the precision engineering of small electronic components, ideal for embedded systems or prototyping.  
<final> A tiny red USB circuit board, labeled with pins and a gear icon, is shown next to a U.S. quarter to emphasize its compact size and suitability for electronics projects.
